        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="103" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Some providers can detect which columns in the row change, but many providers cannot.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="104" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>As a result, updating a column can result in an error when there is a reference to the row you are attempting to update.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="105" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>To solve this problem, create a separate accessor containing only the columns you want to change.</source>
        </trans-unit>
